r%20in%20red%20states.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20a%20majority%20in%20Congress%20and%20support%20from%20the%20West%20Wing%2C%20GOP%20leaders%20will%20decide%20future%20funding%20for%20a%20slew%20of%20federal%20programs%2C%20including%20food%20stamps.%20House%20Republicans%20proposed%20at%20least%20%24230%20billion%20in%20cuts%20to%20federal%20nutrition%20programs%20like%20SNAP%20%E2%80%94%20which%20nearly%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.fns.usda.gov%2Fpd%2Fsupplemental-nutrition-assistance-program-snap%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E42%20million%3C%2Fa%3E%20Americans%20rely%20on%20to%20afford%20food%20%E2%80%94%20over%20the%20next%20decade.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20most%20significant%20policy%20change%20the%20House%20Agriculture%20Committee%20has%20suggested%20would%20require%20nondisabled%20adults%20without%20dependents%20to%20fulfill%20work%20requirements%20until%20they%20reach%20age%2064%20to%20qualify%20for%20aid%2C%20up%20from%20the%20current%20cutoff%20age%20of%2054.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20Republicans%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthehill.com%2Fhomenews%2Fhouse%2F5297278-house-republicans-agriculture-snap%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehave%20defended%20the%20proposal%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20saying%20that%20it%20supports%20Trump's%20goal%20of%20reducing%20waste%20in%20government%20spending.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EIt's%20unclear%20if%20the%20budget%20cuts%20would%20reduce%20the%20monthly%20grocery%20benefits%20that%20households%20receive.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EStill%2C%20advocates%20say%20less%20funding%20and%20stricter%20work%20requirements%20would%20make%20it%20more%20difficult%20for%20millions%20of%20families%20to%20put%20meals%20on%20the%20table%20alongside%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffamily-of-seven-how-to-combat-rising-prices-groceries-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ehigh%20grocery%20prices%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20an%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2FHouseAgGOP%2Fstatus%2F