20of%20trade%20negotiations.%20I%20suppose%20it's%20better%20that%20the%20parties%20involved%20are%20talking%20rather%20than%20not%20talking%2C%20but%20it's%20hard%20for%20any%20firm%20to%20want%20to%20get%20in%20front%20of%20these%20negotiations%20and%20invest%20and%20hire%20now.%20What%20if%20tariff%20rates%20go%20back%20to%20zero%2C%20and%20you%20just%20decided%20to%20make%20a%20large%20commitment%20to%20reorient%20your%20supply%20chain%20logistics%3F%20What%20about%20fears%20that%20any%20deal%20can%20now%20be%20undone%20by%20a%20future%20administration%3F%20Trade%20negotiations%20take%20time%2C%20and%20it's%20unrealistic%20to%20anticipate%20a%20quick%20deal%20that%20has%20teeth.%20Even%20the%20preliminary%20agreements%20with%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-trade-deal-tariffs-uk-announcement-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EUK%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-china-trade-deal-agreement-slash-trump-tariffs-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EChina%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20while%20they%20have%20cooled%20the%20temperature%20somewhat%2C%20represent%20serious%20escalations%20in%20barriers%20compared%20with%20last%20year.%20The%20issue%20is%20how%20much%20damage%20has%20been%20done%20by%20tariffs%2C%20how%20much%20damage%20is%20being%20done%20by%20uncertainty%2C%20and%20how%20much%20damage%20continues%20to%20be%20done%20by%20the%20Fed%20not%20stepping%20out%20to%20assuage%20any%20fears.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20starters%2C%20I%20think%20it's%20best%20to%20focus%20on%20what%20has%20actually%20happened.%20There's%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-2nd-term-calendar-deadlines-key-dates-timeline%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ebaseline%20tariff%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%2010%25%2C%20another%2025%25%20on%20steel%20and%20aluminum%2C%20and%20tariffs%20on%20non-USMCA%20cars%20and%20car%20parts.%20Yes%2C%20the%20US%20and%20China%20have%20backed%20off%20the%20eye-watering%20tariffs%20that%20were%20threatened%20throughout%20April%2C%20but%20a%2030%25%20rate%20is%20still%20exceptionally%20high%2C%20and%20the%20temporary%20nature%20of%20the%20reprieve%20adds%20another%20element%20of%20uncertainty.%20All%20told%2C%20the%20effective%20tariff%20rate%20on%20products%20coming%20into%20the%20US%20is%20still%20roughly%2015%25%2C%20the%20highest%20in%20almost%20a%20century.%20This%20amounts%20to%20a%20meaningful%20shock%20to%20the%20economy%3A%20It%20remains%20to%20be%20seen%20how%20much%20consumer%20prices%20rise%2C%20but%20tariffs%2C%20at%20a%20minimum%2C%20increase%20costs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20if%20a%20continued%20trickle%20of%20deals%20fuels%20the%20stock%20market%20rally%2C%20stock%20prices%20are%20not%20the%20main%20consideration%20for%20labor%20market%20outcomes.%20US%20stocks%20have%20enjoyed%20a%20remarkable%20run%20over%20the%20past%2014%20months%2C%20rising%20roughly%2016%25%20at%20an%20annual%20rate.%20But%20this%20hasn't%20kept%20the%20unemployment%20rate%20from%20rising%200.8%20percentage%20points%20over%20this%20period.%20Put%20differently%2C%20buoyant%20financial%20market%20conditions%20have%20not%20been%20enough%20to%20keep%20the%20labor%20market%20from%20slowing%20in%20the%20first%20place.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20real%20source%20of%20relief%2C%20I%20think%2C%20is%20a%20shift%20in%20the%20Fed's%20interest%20rate%20maneuvers.%20On%20May%207%2C%20Powell%20and%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20Federal%20Open%20Market%20Committee%20left%20rates%20unchanged%20at%204.25%25%20to%204.5%25.%20Even%20though%20it's%20the%20Fed's%20job%20to%20make%20decisions%20with%20imperfect%20information%2C%20it%20remains%20in%20wait-and-see%20mode.%20As%20it%20stands%2C%20the%20growth%20of%20wages%20and%20salaries%20is%20running%20below%20the%20level%20of%20the%20Fed's%20headline%20interest%20rate.%20Historically%2C%20this%20is%20a%20sign%20that%20policy%20is%20too%20restrictive.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20the%20administration%20can%20keep%20up%20the%20pretense%20of%20negotiations%20on%20the%20expectation%20that%20global%20trade%20barriers%20eventually%20will%20come%20down%2C%20it%20might%20see%20the%20markets%20come%20to%20its%20defense%20%E2%80%94%20stocks%20rally%2C%20bond%20yields%20fall.%20If%20that's%20the%20case%2C%20it%20could%20shift%20the%20blame%20for%20the%20jobs%20market%20slowdown%20onto%20the%20Fed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20its%20part%2C%20the%20Fed%20believes%20that%20the%20US%20economy%20is%20expanding%20at%20a%20solid%20pace%20and%20that%20labor%20market%20conditions%20are%20solid%2C%20even%20though%20labor%20demand%20continues%20to%20cool.%20If%20labor%20market%20conditions%20have%20already%20cooled%2C%20what%20makes%20the%20Fed%20assume%20this%20stabilizes%20on%20its%20own%3F%20It%20can't%20and%20won't%2C%20which%20means%20a%20policy%20response%20will%20ultimately%20be%20required.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20investors%2C%20it's%20worth%20highlighting%20that%20the%20labor%20market%20slowdown%20is%20already%20in%20motion%20to%20a%20meaningful%20degree.%20So%20it%20still%20makes%20sense%20to%20be%20defensive%20and%20anticipate%20rate%20cuts%20this%20year%2C%20as%20early%20as%20the%20summer.%20That%20should%20be%20good%20for%20fixed%20income.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Fneil-dutta%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_self%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3ENeil%20Dutta%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20head%20of%20economics%20at%20Renaissance%20Macro%20Research.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famerica-cracking-job-market-layoffs-unemployment-recession-tariffs-2025-5%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1747296182000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6824e33168a2929008015422%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famerica-cracking-job-market-layoffs-unemploym